cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the performance evaluation of a receiver for GFDM, which involves analyzing the signal-to-interference-plus-noise ratio (SINR) and bit error rate (BER) performance. This falls under the purview of information theory.
2. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking): The paper proposes precoding techniques to enhance the performance of GFDM and evaluates the computational complexity of different transmitters and receivers. This is related to the field of communications and networking.
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the challenges faced by OFDM in meeting the requirements of 5G and proposes GFDM as a possible solution. This is related to the field of networking and internet architecture.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with the performance evaluation and optimization of a communication system, which falls under the purview of systems and control.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses the peak to average power ratio (PAPR) reduction techniques for GFDM, which is relevant to the field of multimedia as it affects the quality of transmission.
